PN,37704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1778425867
OL,3,CBirmingham city council leader John
OL,4,CCotton accepts defeat for Labour
OL,6,F"I believe that is a deal that can
OL,7,Fbring this dispute to a close, it's
OL,8,Ffair to the workforce, and brings them
OL,9,Fback to work."
OL,11,FAdmitting this could have been a
OL,12,Fcontributing factor to the loss of his
OL,13,Fseat he said,
OL,15,F"I would have liked to have bought
OL,16,Fthis to a conclusion a lot earlier and
OL,17,Fthat's why we worked so hard to get
OL,18,Fnegotiation settlements.
OL,20,F"Sorry to not have brought this over
OL,21,Fthe line before (we did).
OL,26,@}D@Qpm}D@Xpn
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1778425867
OL,3,CBirmingham city council leader John
OL,4,CCotton accepts defeat for Labour
OL,6,F"However, we had a whole series of
OL,7,Fdifficult issues to work through in
OL,8,Forder to get a settlement that was
OL,9,Ffair to the workforce but also fair to
OL,10,Fthe tax payers of this city."
OL,12,FHe thanked the people of Birmingham,
OL,13,Ffor the privilege of representing the
OL,14,Fonly place he's ever lived and the
OL,15,Fplace he's proud to call home.
OL,17,F"In my mind, Birmingham is still the
OL,18,Fgreatest city in the world and I
OL,19,Fremain a proud Brummie 'til my dying
OL,20,Fday."
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/6
